Title: An Act Regarding Fairness in Sentencing for Persons Under 26
Official Title: An Act Regarding Fairness in Sentencing for Persons Under 26
Number of Sections: 1
Source: versions - Documents and Disposition
Media Type: application/pdf
Strikethrough Detection: 2 sections found

================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1113
H.P. 732 House of Representatives, March 18, 2025
Years of Age
Reference to the Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative WARREN of Scarborough.
Cosponsored by Representatives: HASENFUS of Readfield, LEE of Auburn, MILLIKEN of
Blue Hill, PLUECKER of Warren, PUGH of Portland, SINCLAIR of Bath, YUSUF of
Portland.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 17-A MRSA §1603, sub-§1-A is enacted to read:
3 1-A. Limit on sentence. Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, a
4 person may not be sentenced to imprisonment for life without the possibility of supervised
5 community confinement under Title 34-A, section 3036-A after a period of 15 years if the
6 person was under 26 years of age at the time that the conduct forming the basis for the
7 conviction occurred.
8 Sec. 2. 17-A MRSA §1604, sub-§2, ¶A, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 113, Pt. A, §2,
9 is amended to read:
10 A. In the case of the Class A crime of aggravated attempted murder, the court shall set
11 a term of imprisonment under section 152‑A, subsection 2 of life or a definite period
12 of any term of years, except a person may not be sentenced to imprisonment for life
13 without the possibility of supervised community confinement under Title 34-A, section
14 3036-A after a period of 15 years if the person was under 26 years of age at the time
15 that the conduct forming the basis for the conviction occurred;
16 Sec. 3. 34-A MRSA §3036-A, sub-§2, ¶E is enacted to read:
17 E. Notwithstanding paragraphs A to D, a prisoner may be transferred to supervised
18 community confinement if the prisoner was sentenced to imprisonment for life, served
19 at least 15 years of that sentence and was under 26 years of age at the time that the
20 conduct forming the basis for the conviction occurred.
21 SUMMARY
2222 This bill prohibits a person from being sentenced to imprisonment for life without the
2233 possibility of supervised community confinement after a period of 15 years for a conviction
2244 in which the person was under 26 years of age at the time that the conduct forming the basis
2255 for the conviction occurred.
